Job Details
               In recent years, Myer Emco has made an important shift from an emphasis on the traditional "box" business (seen at most electronics retailers) to a focus on installed systems. As the complexity of these installed systems has evolved, Myer Emco's Systems Installation Group has become increasingly important part of the company. Myer Emco sales associates have always been ready and able to install stereo systems and home theaters at our customers' homes free of charge - a policy which continues to this day!  At the present time, not only is Myer Emco fully capable of installing state-of-the-art home theater systems, we are also involved with multi-room audio/video and home automation systems that are at the cutting-edge of consumer electronics technology. In 1998, the final piece of the Systems Installation Group "puzzle" was added, with the acquisition of Myer Emco Security Systems, one of Washington's finest residential and commercial security companies.  Now we are able to provide a "total solution" to Washington homes - from multi-room audio/video systems, home theaters and security systems, to home telephone and network systems and even highly advanced home automation systems. Our longstanding customers can rest assured that as we continue to change to keep up with and lead the technological changes in the world of consumer electronics, Myer Emco's quality and service will continue to be the finest in Washington, and among the best available anywhere in the United States.
