Executive Profile
Michael E. Recca  Director, Crown Financial Holdings, IncAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Michael E. Recca serves as President, Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director of US Brokerage Operations of Sky Capital Holdings, Ltd. Mr. Recca serves as President of Sky Capital, LLC, a wholly owned subsidiary of Sky Capital Holdings, Ltd. and an NASD broker-dealer. He serves as a member and the sole manager of Harvey Acquisition Company, LLC, which is a principal shareholder of Harvey Electronics Inc. Mr. Recca was an employee of Taglich Brothers, Inc., ... an NASD registered broker-dealer, until December 31, 1998. Beginning in January 2002 and continuing until April 2002, Mr. Recca was self-employed as a financial restructuring Consultant, and in this capacity also associated with NorthStar Capital, LLC, a joint venture with Ruskin Moscou Faltischek, P.C., Harvey Electronics Inc.'s corporate counsel. Mr. Recca has nearly thirty years business experience in the securities and other industries, including retail brokerage, initial public offerings, leveraged buyouts, private placements, bankruptcy reorganizations and mergers and acquisitions. He has extensive experience, nearly ten years, in Private Placements of securities of Public and private companies including the placement of $30 million of debt and equity securities in nine transactions, including PIPE transactions (Private Investments in Public Entities) during the two-year period from 1996 to 1998. Mr. Recca also has extensive experience in reorganizing companies operating under the protection of the Bankruptcy Code, or using the Bankruptcy laws as a means of acquiring or disposing of assets. Most recently, he was the investment banker advising the Chairman of Arnold Industries in the acquisition of the Arnold Industries by Roadway Industries and the acquisition by management of a division of the Arnold Industries for over $100 million. Mr. Recca had been Chairman of the Board of Directors of Harvey Electronics Inc, a specialty retailer in New York City that emerged from Chapter 11 since November 1996 and serves as Director. He served as Interim Chief Executive Officer, Chief Restructuring Officer for Harvey Electronics Inc. He has been a Director of Crown Financial Group Inc., since August 2004. Currently, Mr. Recca serves as a Director of Sky Capital Holdings, Ltd., and of several wholly owned subsidiaries of Sky Capital Holdings. Mr. Recca serves as a Director of Sky Venture Capital and Sky Capital Ventures, (companies affiliated with Sky Capital Holdings, LTD) and several of their wholly or partially owned subsidiaries including Global Secure Holdings, Ltd., and its wholly owned subsidiaries. He served as a Director of Global Secure Corp. since April 2003. Mr. Recca received a B.A. degree in Economics from the State University of New York at Stony Brook in 1972 and a M.B.A. from the Columbia Graduate School of Business in 1974. Read Full Background




